<LEADPARA>  Animal lovers are urged to "come and pet it" this weekend at the Northern
California Pet &amp; Animal Fair at the Santa Clara County Fairgrounds.;    The
weekend fair will feature 75 seminars on topics ranging from pet care to
training. The feeding and grooming needs of dogs and cats will be addressed as
well as the care of more exotic animals such as llamas, miniature pot-belly
pigs and exotic killfish. Animal behaviorists, veterinarians, breeders and
trainers will give lectures.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  East Extra  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  FAIR FUR ANIMAL LOVERS PLANNED FUR THIS
WEEKEND  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Also ran in EX2/2, EX3/2, EX4/3, WT2
Animals  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Although there will be pets for sale, the focus of the show is on pet
education, training and care, said Linda West of the Los Gatos-based company
producing the show. The company plans to make this fair an annual event.;   
"We had talked to over a hundred people about the types of shows they'd like
to see produced," West said. "Pets came up the most often.";    Contests,
including a pet-owner look-alike competition, a top cat contest and a most
talented pet contest will also take place.;    Admission is $6 for adults, $5
for seniors and $4 for children. A portion of the show's proceeds will be
donated to the Humane Society of Santa Clara Valley, Pets-in-Need and the Jane
Goodall Institute.;    For more information, call (408) 354-0700.  </TEXT>
